5. Non-Functional Requirements
This section specifies the non-functional requirements of the Student Internship Portal. These requirements define quality attributes that the system must exhibit, including usability, performance, security, reliability, and maintainability. Each requirement is specific, measurable, and verifiable.

5.1 Usability
Usability requirements address the ease of learning, ease of use, error recovery, and accessibility of the system for all user classes.

•	USE-1: The system shall provide a responsive web interface that adapts correctly to screen resolutions ranging from 320px (mobile) to 1920px (desktop) without loss of functionality or readability.
•	USE-2: The system shall allow a new user to complete the registration process within 3 minutes, without requiring external documentation or assistance.
•	USE-3: All error messages displayed by the system shall be descriptive, specific, and provide actionable guidance to help users correct their input.
•	USE-4: The system shall provide a consistent navigation menu accessible on all pages, enabling users to reach any section of their dashboard within two clicks from the homepage.
•	USE-5: The system shall use standard web form conventions (labels, placeholder text, required field indicators) to minimize user input errors.
•	USE-6: The system shall display confirmation messages upon successful completion of all critical actions, including registration, profile updates, CV uploads, and application submissions.

5.2 Performance
Performance requirements define the expected speed, responsiveness, and throughput of the system under normal and peak operating conditions.

•	PER-1: 95% of all web pages generated by the system shall load completely within 3 seconds over a 10 Mbps or faster internet connection under normal load conditions.
•	PER-2: The system shall support at least 200 concurrent user sessions without significant performance degradation (response time increase of no more than 20%).
•	PER-3: Internship search queries shall return results within 2 seconds for datasets containing up to 10,000 internship records.
•	PER-4: File upload operations (CV uploads) shall complete within 10 seconds for files up to the maximum allowed size of 5 MB on a standard broadband connection.
•	PER-5: The system shall process application submissions and update the database record within 1 second of the user's submission action.

5.3 Security
Security requirements define the measures the system must implement to protect user data, prevent unauthorized access, and ensure data integrity.

•	SEC-1: The system shall encrypt all user passwords using Django's default PBKDF2 hashing algorithm with a SHA-256 hash function before storing them in the database.
•	SEC-2: All data transmission between the client and server shall be secured using HTTPS (TLS 1.2 or higher) to prevent interception of sensitive information.
•	SEC-3: The system shall implement Django's built-in Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) protection on all forms and state-changing requests.
•	SEC-4: The system shall enforce role-based access control (RBAC), ensuring that Students, Companies, and Administrators can only access features and data corresponding to their assigned role.
•	SEC-5: The system shall validate and sanitize all user-provided inputs on both the client side and server side to prevent SQL injection, XSS, and other injection-based attacks.
•	SEC-6: User sessions shall expire after 30 minutes of inactivity, requiring re-authentication to resume.

5.4 Reliability
Reliability requirements define the expected uptime, fault tolerance, and data recovery capabilities of the system.

•	REL-1: The system shall achieve an uptime of at least 99% on a monthly basis, excluding scheduled maintenance windows.
•	REL-2: The system shall perform automated database backups every 24 hours to prevent data loss in the event of a system failure.
•	REL-3: In the event of a server-side error, the system shall display a user-friendly error page and log the error details for administrator review, without exposing sensitive system information to the user.
•	REL-4: The system shall handle concurrent write operations (multiple simultaneous application submissions) without data corruption or loss, using Django's ORM transaction management.

5.5 Maintainability
Maintainability requirements define how easily the system can be modified, extended, and debugged by developers after initial deployment.

•	MNT-1: The system code shall be organized into separate Django applications by functional module (accounts, students, companies, internships, applications, admin) to facilitate independent development and testing.
•	MNT-2: All code shall be documented with inline comments and docstrings following Python PEP 257 conventions to enable future developers to understand and modify the system efficiently.
•	MNT-3: The system shall use Django's built-in admin interface as the foundation for administrative features, enabling rapid configuration without code changes.
•	MNT-4: The system shall be version-controlled using Git, with all changes committed with descriptive messages to maintain a clear development history.

 
